==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cerinthian
<hw>Ce*rin"thi*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One
of an ancient religious sect, so called from <etsep>Cerinthus</etsep>, a
Jew, who attempted to unite the doctrines of Christ with the opinions of
the Jews and Gnostics.</def> <rj><au>Hook.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ceriph</ent>⟦br⟧
